7258, "(fr)No, sir! I just wanted to express my thanks, and convey my wishes that Admiral Byrne would grow the balls to make this decision himself."

7259, "(fr)My time with the Wargods has given me something to believe in, sir: the men and women alongside me. And, for the record, I wish Admiral Byrne had the balls to make this decision himself. I'm with you, sir."

7260, "(fr)Sublieutenant Laporte, your willingness to speak ill of a superior officer in an undisciplined tirade fills me with..."

7261, "(fr)...a certain ill-advised respect. Consider yourself forgiven. Possibly even acknowledged."

7262, "(fr)Now get the Agincourt through that gate before Steele disentangles himself and comes running to save his career."

7263, "(fr)My God, Laporte, you're still on flight status. I can't believe Calder let you off."

7264, "(fr)Nice speech, Sublieutenant. Did you have that all written out on some flowered stationery? Taped up in your cockpit?"

7265, "(fr)I bet he loved your input, Laporte. He'll probably make you Special Requisitions Officer for Byrne's Testicles or something."

7266, "(fr)Oh, hush. You know how I get on combat high."

7267, "(fr)All right, Wargods. Looks like we're going to win this war all on our own. Let's jump home and get started."

7268, "(fr)Uh-oh, there goes the Anjaneya. We've lost our ECM cover. Someone needs to nail the Hood's forward beams once this wave passes."

7269, "(fr)Anjaneya here! If we go down, the Hood will vaporize this task force! Give us cover!"

7270, "(fr)Here they come, Wargods!"

