7315, "(fr)Good lord...what a ship..."

7316, "(fr)The Buntu are here! All fighters, break off! We need to haul ass!"

7317, "(fr)Our boarding party's getting cut up here, Boss! Bloody huge Vasudans and their enormous guns! They've got some kind of power armour...Gaia, it's got a fucking sword!"

7318, "(fr)I didn't sign up for this shit! We're getting out of here!"

7319, "(fr)Marines, you must get clear of the airlock! We're reading an explosive device inside the dock!"

7320, "(fr)Detonation detected. Marines, report your status!"

7321, "(fr)This is Tactical Two. We have suffered major casualties. The explosion buckled several bulkheads and left multiple compartments open to space."

7322, "(fr)Retreat, retreat! This operation's gone to hell!"

7323, "(fr)Those Gef bastards bit off more than they could chew. I wonder what drove them to attack the Vasudans...didn't we think they were working for the Tevs?"

7324, "(fr)Pesedjet, this is Captain Sorensen of the UEFg Indus, Second Fleet Mars. We received your distress signal and are here to provide assistance. What is your status?"

7325, "(fr)You are speaking to Captain Apries of the Pesedjet. The Gef boarding party inflicted damage to our fuel processors. We have multiple cases of radiation exposure and flash burns. Our emergency response teams have been overwhelmed."

7326, "(fr)CIC, this is Engineering. Reactor containment has been compromised. We have multiple cases of radiation exposure and flash burns. Our emergency response teams have been overwhelmed."

7327, "(fr)We've got a medical transport on two-minute standby, Captain Apries. Our medics have been brought up to speed on Vasudan physiology. Permission to proceed."

7328, "(fr)Permission denied, Captain Sorensen. Under GTVA protocol, we cannot submit our vessel to your authority."

7329, "(fr)We're not asking for your surrender, Captain Apries. Federation policy is to offer support to all neutral vessels in distress. Our hands are open."

7330, "(fr)This is not a neutral vessel. Under the Deneb Convention, your government is designated a hostile power. As such, we have no choice but to respond to any attempted boardings with force."

7331, "(fr)Are...are the Vasudans rejecting our medical assistance? Are they insane?"

7332, "(fr)Think about it this way, Levi. The Gefs are a lot like their Hammer of Light. Would you let a bunch of Vasudans board your ship after an attack by those nutjobs?"

7333, "(fr)If we're falling back on technicalities, Captain, last I checked our government was at war with the General Terran Assembly, not the Imperium. Consider this a token of friendship from a society that shares much in common with your own."

7334, "(fr)We have no quarrel with your Emperor. "

7335, "(fr)Your actions are honourable, Captain Sorensen, but I cannot help but doubt your intentions. We are quite aware of the role that your ship played in the capture of the GTL Agincourt."

7336, "(fr)I'm sure you'll see the difference between action against an enemy target and a mission of mercy, Pesedjet. Scan the Littman, and you'll find no weapons on board."

7337, "(fr)Your medical ship appears to be what it seems, Captain Sorensen. Our situation leaves us little choice. Send the Littman, and only the Littman, to the port dock. I will have a marine detachment meet your medical team at the airlock."

7338, "(fr)Ladies and gentlemen of the Indus Wargods. Looks like we're privileged enough to witness the first contact between Earth and Vasudan forces in fifty years."

7339, "(fr)Their ship...it's as though someone took a sea creature, blew it up to destroyer proportions and installed some turrets on the outside. Vasudan craftsmanship to the core."

7340, "(fr)Similar, but at the same time not like the Tevs. You can tell Tev ships are war machines, they have a sort of deadly beauty to them. The Vasudans have the same beauty, but none of the menace."

7341, "(fr)I'd do anything just to talk to one of them. I've read stories about their culture. Martin Mandho said that Khonsu was closer to spiritual enlightenment than many of our Elders."

7342, "(fr)Spiritually enlightened or not, their beams are going to be just as terrifying when they're aimed at our ships. Until they're helping us kick the Tevs out of our system, I'm not going to expect a damned thing from them."

7343, "(fr)Really, Captain? There's no curiosity down under all that Martian gruff? Permit me to quote the intel database: 'a civilization of philosophers, artists, and scholars.' You're not intrigued?"

7344, "(fr)I once attended a lecture given by one of the Epsilon Four. He answered questions afterwards about what it was like being one of the only Vasudans left in Sol. Of course, they say the Vasudans were with the Fedayeen..."

7345, "(fr)Khonsu invited the Epsilon Four to Aldebaran for a ceremony of honour. They all received an Imperial Order of Vasuda, last I heard."

7346, "(fr)Really, Laporte? That's pretty neat. How did you find this out?"

7347, "(fr)Captain Sorensen, we're picking up a jump point forming nearby! Hostile configuration!"

7348, "(fr)Looks like the Tevs got the distress call too. All crew to battlestations! Fighter wings, take up escort positions around the Indus and Littman. Do not engage unless fired upon."

7349, "(fr)Weapons hold, Alpha and Beta wings! Do not fire until I say! Keep away from those Tev ships."

7350, "(fr)GTCv Arethusa to Federation vessels. The Pesedjet is under our protection. Stand down your vessels and leave, or we will open fire."

7351, "(fr)This is Captain Sorensen of the UEFg Indus. Negative on your demands, Arethusa. We are engaged in a medical mission and will defend ourselves."

7352, "(fr)Damned Tev! Get off my tail! Indus control, permission to open fire!"

7353, "(fr)Don't make me laugh, Captain. Medical mission? This is clearly another attack on our logistics by a desperate military. Leave now, or suffer the consequences."

7354, "(fr)Captain Price, we can vouch for their actions thus far. The Indus and her fighters assisted in driving off an attack by the Gaian Effort. We are transmitting logs."

7355, "(fr)Acknowledged, Pesedjet. We believe some Gaian Effort cells may be working for the Federation's black ops unit. This is likely an attempt on your ship."

7356, "(fr)Their teams aboard my vessel are unarmed. They did not exhibit any suspicious behavior."

7357, "(fr)These records seem to check out, Captain Apries. But we've got bigger problems. Your ship's hull integrity is dropping fast. We need to deploy teams to help contain internal fires and lock down damage."

7358, "(fr)Captain Sorenson, unless you want a firefight aboard a dying ship, withdraw at once. Your rescue efforts are neither welcome nor needed. We will use force if necessary."

7359, "(fr)We don't have time for this, Captain. These Vasudans are in need of medical assistance! Unless you want to explain to the Emperor why his soldiers had to die, let us do our jobs!"

7360, "(fr)WARNING: LONG RANGE COMMUNICATIONS DISABLED. RUNNING DIAGNOSTICS."

7361, "(fr)Holy - Indus control, I'm getting red lights on my board. Long-range communications are down!"

7362, "(fr)Captain Sorensen, we don't have time for this posturing! The clock's ticking on the Pesedjet's reactor failure!"

7363, "(fr)Captain Price, we're picking up massive jamming from your corvette. What is the meaning of this?"

7364, "(fr)A little insurance policy, Captain Sorensen. You want to do things your way, fine. Help out the Vasudans, but no reinforcements."

7365, "(fr)GTT Sampson, on approach to dock with Pesedjet's ventral airlock. Federation forces, if you are armed, hold your fire."

7366, "(fr)In which case, Captain, I'm sure you won't object to us returning the favour. Comms, hit them with a wide-frequency blast. Jam their long-ranged communications."

7367, "(fr)This is Medic Team Alpha! We're experiencing massive internal detonations! The Vasudan engineers we're patching up say that internal safeties have failed!"

7368, "(fr)Damn! We're scrambling repair equipment from the Indus, but it's going to be several minutes before we can load a shuttle. Do the best you can with what you have."

7369, "(fr)We've got repair technicians with heavy field equipment on board the Sampson. Standard procedure for answering a stricken vessel. You could learn from our example next time."

7370, "(fr)And your transport carries only the barest medical facilities, Captain. If your engineers save the ship, we'll save the crew. Once the Pesedjet is out of danger...we'll work from there."

7371, "(fr)Touche, Captain Sorensen."

7372, "(fr)Touche, Captain Sorensen. Here's my proposal. We stand down, and you do the same. We pool our resources, repair this Vasudan ship, and then we go our separate ways."

7373, "(fr)The Vasudans continue to help us supply, while you gain favour with Khonsu for when you negotiate the terms of your surrender."

7374, "(fr)Indus, I'm reading a global weapons power down on the Arethusa and Tev fighters. They've disengaged and are pulling back."

7375, "(fr)What extraordinary times we live in. Very well, Captain Price. The welfare of the Pesedjet will take precedence for now. However, if you do anything to compromise the ceasefire, we will not hesitate to open fire."

7376, "(fr)Red and black ants, building bowling alleys together from caterpillar teeth."

7377, "(fr)This is doing my head in. Sitting this close to Tevs without shots firing."

7378, "(fr)Normally I'd be itching to open fire, but...do you think this is how it was supposed to be? That maybe this is the first sane thing that's happened since the Tevs showed up?"

7379, "(fr)This is Medic Team Alpha. Engineer crisis teams have managed to seal off compromised areas. Radiation levels are falling, and we've managed to secure most of the surviving crew. Good thing those techs came when they did."

7380, "(fr)Ever the romantic, Laporte. Frankly, this is absurd. Sooner or later we'll be shooting at each other again. Let's just get it over with."

7381, "(fr)If you ask me, a little danger brings a certain buzz to first meetings. Has anyone ever told you how lovely you sound on the comm?"

7382, "(fr)Lieutenant Fabian Kurniadi. at your service. 181st Bloodhounds squadron, GTD Carthage. Callsign 'Anansi'...goodness knows why."

7383, "(fr)Captain Lorna Simms, Indus Wargods. Now you'll know who I am when our little hugbox breaks up and I kill you."

7384, "(fr)Only one side can win. Choose."

7385, "(fr)..."

7386, "(fr)It is the way of things. You must choose."

7387, "(fr)Sublieutenant Noemi Laporte, Indus Wargods. Have a care with Captain Simms, Tev. You don't want her on the wrong side of the IFF spectrum."

7388, "(fr)So I've heard. Your squadron has Admiral Steele's attention, Sublieutenant Laporte. You lot seem determined to win this war all by yourself."

7389, "(fr)It's always good to verify our strategic impact from a human source, Lieutenant Kurniadi. How about some hard numbers? What's the bounty on my head? "

7390, "(fr)Big enough to make me take notice, and my father's a shipping magnate. The catch is, of course, that no one survives to collect...or I'm sure I would have heard reports of your charms."

7391, "(fr)This is a bad line of work for an amateur Casanova, Lieutenant. When you get shot down out here, it's dangerously literal."

7392, "(fr)Medic Team Alpha here. Preliminary triage has been completed. We're moving the critically wounded onto the Littman for emergency care. I wish to state for the record that the conduct of GTVA engineering teams has been more than exemplary."

7393, "(fr)Acknowledged, MT Alpha. Good work. Well, Captain Price, it seems thanks are in order."

7394, "(fr)Eyes up pilots, new contact! It's the heavy frigate Hesperia!"

7395, "(fr)Priority message to Captain Aldred. Tell him to cease fire immediately, the Arethusa is a non-combatant!"

7396, "(fr)Scorpio wing and the Arethusa have gone weapons hot!"

7397, "(fr)Littman, you are to disengage from the Pesedjet. We're pulling you out of the battlezone."

7398, "(fr)Commencing undocking process now. Be advised, we've got Vasudan wounded on board. Captain Apries has demanded that we return them before we undock."

7399, "(fr)There's no time, Littman. Get out of there now, before the Tevs make you a target!"

7400, "(fr)Pilots, evasive manoeuvres! Watch the fire, it's close quarters at the moment!"

7401, "(fr)The Arethusa has opened fire!"

7402, "(fr)So much for a ceasefire. All batteries, return fire. Fighters, form a defensive screen!"

7403, "(fr)The Littman has made it out. Pilots, follow us back to Mars on the double!"

7404, "(fr)Oh, damn it...Tev fighters on an attack run! The Arethusa has opened fire!"

7405, "(fr)We surrender, you traitorous sons of bitches! Hold your fire!"

7406, "(fr)Hesperia, this is the Indus. The Arethusa was assisting our humanitarian mission for the Pesedjet. You've just destroyed a non-combatant under a ceasefire."

7407, "(fr)Ceasefire? Pardon me, Captain Sorensen, but I got no notice from Command that such a ceasefire was in place. Admiral Calder deployed us to secure the area after we lost contact with you. The Arethusa was a hostile target, and by definition a combatant."

7408, "(fr)Seems like the status quo has returned to this little area of space, Laporte. How do you fancy the outcome of this 'humanise the enemy' experiment?"

7409, "(fr)I can't complain, One. We're still alive. But I can't help but wonder what would have happened if it had lasted a little longer..."

7410, "(fr)Still, I guess best intentions aren't enough to stop the fighting. It's too late for that. This war won't end until one side wins...and I'd rather it be us."

7411, "(fr)Laporte, we'll make a Martian of you yet."

7412, "(fr)Pilots, this mission is over. Bring yourselves in. Gamma wing from the Hesperia will take over escort duty."

7413, "(fr)<ALERT. incoming transmission: tight beam, single target. source: Pesedjet dorsal array 16. stand by>"

7414, "(fr)Accept the transmission. Tell no one."

7415, "(fr)Oh, what the hell..."

7416, "(fr)ACCEPTING SIGNAL. DOWNLOADING TO FLEETNET SECURE PERSONAL STORE...COMPLETE. CLEARING TRANSMISSION LOGS."

7417, "(fr)Noemi Laporte: this is a gift from the enemies of your enemy. You will know when you need it. <encrypted datafile attached>"

7418, "(fr)The Arethusa is going down...that last volley got her magazines and safeties."

7419, "(fr)Mayday, mayday, Anansi is hit - "

