7974, "(fr)You want answers. What we want. Who you are.

You will learn these things. They are secondary. You must master that which makes you $f Fedayeen: the capacity for violence, and the knowledge of when to use that violence. You must be ready to commit atrocities if necessary, and you must nonetheless understand that they are atrocities.

Nothing is true. All actions are permitted. But not all actions are correct. In every moment, you must find the shortest path to our ultimate goal. Ruthlessness, mercy, torture, succor, hatred, compassion: these are all tools, to be deployed as they are needed.

Our single overriding goal is the survival of mankind. The $f Council $f of $f Elders has made it clear to us that if the $f United $f Earth $f Federation is lost, that objective will fail. We intend to learn why."

7975, "(fr)Recent events left you critically damaged. You feel that our prospects in this war are also crippled. But we have a new asset.

We count amongst our ranks four $v Vasudan pilots, stranded in Sol after they helped destroy the $r Lucifer. Their appreciation of the $r Shivan threat led them to help found the $f Fedayeen.

Days before the Fall of Jupiter, they left Sol on the invitation of $v Emperor $v Khonsu $v II. Once they reached $v Aldebaran, these $f Fedayeen completed a pact that began with secret radio transmissions between Alpha Centauri and Earth thirty years ago. The $f Hammer $f of $f Light has come to our aid. We have access to a fanatically loyal intelligence network built deep into the fabric of the $r GTVA's military.

The critical moment of the war is upon us. The Elders have at last authorized us to act without restriction."

