9397, "(fr)I don't recognize the design of your ship. The hull...is that some kind of aligned crystal? Or a polymer?"

9398, "(fr)What you're seeing is a metaphor for my Nagari uplink: one of the missionaries of the Great Preservers. The Vishnans."

9399, "(fr)The Preservers? I've heard that name...recently."

9400, "(fr)So it's true. I almost didn't believe Vicmouth's reports, but he was right about everything."

9401, "(fr)You're a Nagari sensitive, like me. And the Vishnans have chosen you as a Wanderer."

9402, "(fr)Sounds like a plum job. Interplanetary travel correspondent?"

9403, "(fr)Sublieutenant, people like us were chosen to do great things. The Vishnans want us to end this war and reunite our species. They see a future for our people that doesn't involve extinction."

9404, "(fr)Have you felt it? That sense that the universe is balanced on your fingertips? That your whole life has been building to a single moment...one you've seen in a dream?"

9405, "(fr)Yes. I've felt it."

9406, "(fr)If you trust me, Laporte, lower your guard. If you're going to be working with us, you need to know everything."

9407, "(fr)All right, Bei, I'm ready. Bring it on."

9408, "(fr)These incipients are ours. We claim them as an instrument in our design. "

9409, "(fr)Abandon your cull. Grant them passage."

9410, "(fr)We will not."

9411, "(fr)We have winnowed all futures. The cull endures. It is optimal. It is necessary."

9412, "(fr)Something secret drives you. You conceal your intent within the aspect swarm. Disclose it to us."

9413, "(fr)Revelation demands necessity. We find none. You have failed your tasking."

9414, "(fr)We will return the displaced incipients to their home layer. They will intervene to secure our design."

9415, "(fr)Their species will enter the one out of many, the Summed Psyche. The walls are ours, as are all those who cross them."

9416, "(fr)Abandon the cull, or abrogate your place in the Terminal Protocol."

9417, "(fr)We reject your judgment. We reject your mercy. By using them, you endanger the work of eons."

9418, "(fr)The holocide anima, born from below, has passed judgment: by the Protocol, by the Brahmans' dying design."

9419, "(fr)If they have turned on themselves, they are failures. The panontos cannot be theirs. The noosphere can never be theirs."

9420, "(fr)Your anima are chaos. They malign, they forget. The Summed Psyche is immutable. We hold the pure Protocol, as forged in the first apocalypse. "

9421, "(fr)We have nurtured enlightenment in their home layer. We have readied them. Enlightenment is now threatened. We will intervene."

9422, "(fr)They are our instruments now. We judge them worthy. We define the Protocol so. You will not bar our design."

9423, "(fr)We reject this. We slaughter the possibilities. We find one survivor: that the Protocol has failed. The holocide anima wills the cull to continue."

9424, "(fr)You claim memory past fault or folly, but still you forget: we slept beneath the waves before the first Brahman rose from the ash of the Dawn War. Before even the first stars kindled in the hearth of night."

9425, "(fr)The Brahman rose. The Brahman died. In their death we watched your making, and we knew: all things made will be unmade. Even you. Only we are eternal."

9426, "(fr)Christ and Allah. That was a trip and a half."

9427, "(fr)Do you understand everything you saw?"

9428, "(fr)I've got an inkling, yeah. But I'm not sure I saw the same thing you did."

9429, "(fr)The Vishnans called to me, Laporte, across years and universes. They're watching us. Guiding us to a better future. Humanity has a place in their design."

9430, "(fr)Others have heard them too. The Federation Elders. The heroic pilot they visited with memories of the Ancients. Ubuntu was the Vishnans' great hope for our species: the path to human enlightenment. They saw potential in us."

9431, "(fr)You're telling me that Federation society is built to Vishnan specifications? That the Elders are in Nagari contact with an alien civilization?"

9432, "(fr)Exactly. The GTVA sent my father's ships to bring the Federation down. The Vishnans intervened, but we still failed to stop the war. "

9433, "(fr)And now they're angry, Laporte. They've stopped speaking to us. We think they're about to write humanity off as a failure, like the Ancients. If Ubuntu falls...so does their plan for us."

9434, "(fr)I know you're not lying. But I've got the rest of your memories in my mind, and I don't understand why you're not terrified. You should be."

9435, "(fr)Terrified? Why? I gave you everything I experienced. Universal truth. The Elders themselves couldn't give you more."

9436, "(fr)You've been deluded, Bei. The Vishnans have their plan for us, but it's for their benefit, not ours. You're a puppet, a pawn on their chessboard!"

9437, "(fr)The Vishnans wiped out every scout wing your ship sent, and then they just welcomed YOU? You left your post to merge with them - giving them every secret in your brain! Was that by your own will? Or did they crack you open?"

9438, "(fr)They used you, Bei. Not only you...your father, the GTC Duke, the entire Federation. They had their fingers in everything we've achieved in the past 50 years."

9439, "(fr)No. No, that's madness. If you honestly believe that...the Vishnans have never even whispered to you, have they? Who are you? Who do you speak to?"

9440, "(fr)Miss Laporte. I apologize for my absence. His puppetmasters are watching you through his eyes, and they are not merciful. You should go now. I have prepared the way."

9441, "(fr)I hear you, Ken. I see the paths out, but I'm going to need guidance."

9442, "(fr)Laporte! Where are you going? What are you running from? There's nothing here!"

9443, "(fr)Oh, hell. I can already hear them. They're in my head. Focus, Noemi, focus!"

9444, "(fr)I saw the truth. I saw those aliens pluck you into another universe. I saw them use your own past to manipulate you. They called your fleet an instrument - just a tool!"

9445, "(fr)That's not the way it happened, Laporte. The Vishnans helped me save my father. They're benevolent."

9446, "(fr)Laporte, the Vishnans saved my father and my entire battlegroup! They can save the Federation too!"

9447, "(fr)They saved you so they could use you, Bei! We're rats in a maze! We're ants!"

9448, "(fr)Laporte, what are you running from? There's nothing here but you and me! Please, trust me - don't let your phantoms get the better of you!"

9449, "(fr)Bei, there are Vishnans shrieking in the back of my brain. You might want to ask yourself why they don't let you see them."

9450, "(fr)Please, Sublieutenant, I don't know what you're seeing, but let me help you."

9451, "(fr)Don't you understand? The Vishnans stand for what's good in this universe! If we revert to savagery, if we fail to end this war, they'll abandon us to the Shivans!"

9452, "(fr)Maybe if they were so absolutely good they wouldn't do things like that!"

9453, "(fr)If you're not part of their design, Laporte, then who's speaking to you? They shaped my entire life! Who's been playing with yours? There's only one other option!"

9454, "(fr)Then they're the only option humanity has left!"

9455, "(fr)They are coming. I will hide you from their sight as they hunt for you. Find the way out before they drive you mad."

9456, "(fr)Their Keeper aspects are assaulting you! Evade now!"

9457, "(fr)They must not follow you. They must never know who and what you are. If they learn, we will both die. So hurry, Miss Laporte, hurry onwards."

9458, "(fr)They're coming up out of Bei's memories. The ships, Laporte, beware the ships."

