9470, "(fr)Welcome to Capella, Miss Laporte. I'm glad you arrived intact. We were all very worried for you."

9471, "(fr)So many years of careful work to make you, and we came so close to disaster. You could have gone mad in the Nagari dream. The Vishnans could have compromised you. You could have died in the war."

9472, "(fr)But now, at last, you are here. And I think it is safe for us to begin. So, Miss Laporte: ask, and I answer."

9473, "(fr)Tell me what I am. Tell me why I see you. Why I hear your voice."

9474, "(fr)You are an engineered agent, a human mind cultivated into a weapon in the greater war. There are others, there have always been others...but your chances of success are highest."

9475, "(fr)You were shaped by my hand alone. You do not bear the mark of the Shivans, destroyers and preservers both. You are a deniable asset."

9476, "(fr)There is a great rift in the heavens, Miss Laporte. A desperate design begins to founder. The Shivans will grant us a form of survival...and in exchange, you will strike at the only enemy they cannot touch. Your mind is built for it."

9477, "(fr)I know who you are. The name...it was staring me in the face the whole time. You're Admiral Aken Bosch."

9478, "(fr)No. Not Bosch. He is within me, yes, but Miss Laporte, the Shivans do not think as we do. I was engineered to serve as a bridge between their cognition and ours. "

9479, "(fr)Bosch's memories and personalities are part of this anima. So are those of Gibson, Sarno, and thirteen others the Shivans took from the Iceni. I am the dream of many minds...like your Al-Da'wa, who exists only as the gestalt spirit of the Fedayeen."

9480, "(fr)Bosch foresaw his fate. He uncovered GTI's secrets after the Hades rebellion. He created the technology to enable communication between the Shivans and the human race...and now he has become part of that technology."

9481, "(fr)You warned me that if the Federation lost the war humanity would go extinct. You told me I could stop it. How? What do I have to do?"

9482, "(fr)The Vishnans had a design for humanity. Ubuntu was a key element - a vector they used to reengineer our society and behavior. But they see the civil war as a mark of unforgivable failure. They have ordered a cull."

9483, "(fr)The Shivans and Vishnans are bound together by the Terminal Protocol - a cosmos-spanning plan to stave off a second apocalypse. But the plan is failing. The Shivans have...an alternative."

9484, "(fr)The Protocol demands the annihilation of species that do not meet its criteria. There is only one way to stop the cull - the pact that Aken Bosch struck with the Shivans to end the Second Incursion. You are the key, Laporte, the weapon they need."

9485, "(fr)If human survival depends on the Federation's victory, then maybe we can win this war. Tell me how to defeat the Alliance."

9486, "(fr)This war is full of hidden purposes. The most secret element of the Alliance invasion strategy is Contingency Morpheus: their plan to purge Vishnan-compromised elements from human society. The Elders are their prime target."

9487, "(fr)And your Federation has its own designs. Your Elders knew the Destroyers could rebuild collapsed jump nodes. Their Project Shambhala was an answer to that threat...now it is something more."

9488, "(fr)You will need a power base. Begin with the Fedayeen - they understand the calculus of survival. The Hammer of Light answers to the whispers of the Shivan animae. Rally your own military. You will need an armada to achieve your mission."

9489, "(fr)Holy shit. Of course. CASSANDRA is a Shivan body...it can host a Shivanlike mind."

9490, "(fr)Let me see if I've got this straight."

9491, "(fr)I'm a living weapon engineered by a Frankenmind built from a bunch of rebels and their GTI messiah, meant to be used as a payload in a bargain between humanity and the Shivans."

9492, "(fr)Humanity is going to be annihilated by mindless aliens because we don't meet the arbitrary standards of some five billion year old plan - unless we can somehow complete that bargain."

9493, "(fr)Yes."

9494, "(fr)Well, it's good to know the truth. I'm completely insane. And this needs to end before I do any more damage."

9495, "(fr)Miss Laporte! Wait!"

9496, "(fr)Shut up! You were never real! You're some kind of - pathological manifestation, some kind of psychosis."

9497, "(fr)I'm in control. I set the terms here. This - this is where I should've died."

9498, "(fr)I'm not waking up until you're gone or I'm dead. One way or another, you're done fucking with me."

9499, "(fr)<vital signs warning: seizure underway>"

9500, "(fr)Your mind is destroying itself. You will never recover, Miss Laporte. In a few moments you will be past the point of no return."

9501, "(fr)Good. I was supposed to die here, at Saturn, with my friends. Not live on in some kind of...megalomaniac delusion."

9502, "(fr)You must live. The window of opportunity is narrow, and you are the only instrument available. Unless you strike the target, humanity will be extinguished!"

9503, "(fr)Survivor's guilt. I lived when the others died. because I abandoned them - so I constructed a reason for it. I had to live so humanity would endure. Kind of clever, really. But a lie."

9504, "(fr)There is something that has been hidden from you, Laporte. A contingency...a reason for you to live. Al-Da'wa knows. And now, so do I."

9505, "(fr)Lorna Simms is alive."

9506, "(fr)Give in to madness here, and you will never see her again. Accept your purpose, and you may. I beg you, Miss Laporte - make the right choice."

